üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 7: Protecting IS, Mobile & Wireless Security, Credit Card Frauds, IS Management, IS Fundamentals
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Protecting Information System Security mainly involves:
A. Only encryption
B. Only firewalls
C. Policies, controls, and technologies
D. Hardware upgrade

2. Mobile computing security is challenging mainly because of:
A. High speed
B. Portability and wireless connectivity
C. Strong encryption
D. Limited apps

3. Wireless communication is more vulnerable than wired because it:
A. Uses fiber
B. Uses shared air medium
C. Is faster
D. Is encrypted

4. Credit card fraud in mobile computing usually targets:
A. Hardware
B. Network devices
C. User financial information
D. Operating system

5. Information Security Management focuses on:
A. Writing malware
B. Managing security risks
C. Network routing
D. Software testing

6. Which is a core objective of information security?
A. Performance
B. Usability
C. Confidentiality
D. Scalability

7. Which device is MOST vulnerable to theft-related attacks?
A. Desktop
B. Server
C. Mobile phone
D. Router

8. Wireless security mainly protects against:
A. Physical damage
B. Eavesdropping
C. Hardware failure
D. Power loss

9. Credit card fraud is an attack on:
A. Availability
B. Integrity
C. Confidentiality
D. All of the above

10. Fundamentals of information security are based on:
A. OSI model
B. CIA triad
C. TCP/IP
D. ISO model

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which wireless attack captures data transmitted over air?
A. Phishing
B. Sniffing
C. Spoofing
D. Flooding

12. Mobile malware can steal credit card data by:
A. Physical damage
B. Keylogging
C. DoS
D. Port scanning

13. Which control helps prevent mobile device misuse?
A. IDS
B. MDM (Mobile Device Management)
C. NAT
D. Proxy

14. Information Security Management includes:
A. Risk assessment
B. Threat analysis
C. Security policies
D. All of the above

15. Credit card fraud MOST commonly exploits:
A. Hardware bugs
B. User negligence
C. Strong authentication
D. Encryption

16. Which wireless protocol provides encryption?
A. HTTP
B. FTP
C. WPA2
D. Telnet

17. Protecting information systems requires:
A. Only technical controls
B. Only administrative controls
C. Technical, administrative & physical controls
D. Antivirus only

18. Mobile devices increase security risk because they are:
A. Fixed
B. Easily lost or stolen
C. Encrypted
D. Expensive

19. Which is an example of administrative control?
A. Firewall
B. Encryption
C. Security policy
D. IDS

20. Credit card fraud using fake wireless access points is called:
A. Smishing
B. Evil Twin attack
C. Shoulder surfing
D. Pharming

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE TRAP ZONE
21. Wireless security failure MOST directly affects:
A. Integrity
B. Availability
C. Confidentiality
D. Authentication

22. Why mobile devices are harder to secure than desktops?
A. Lower performance
B. Diverse OS & apps
C. Wired connectivity
D. Larger size

23. Credit card fraud through malicious apps violates:
A. Availability
B. Integrity
C. Confidentiality
D. All of the above

24. Information Security Management differs from technical security because it:
A. Uses firewalls
B. Focuses on governance & risk
C. Encrypts data
D. Blocks ports

25. Which attack exploits open Wi-Fi to steal card details?
A. DoS
B. MITM
C. SQL Injection
D. Buffer overflow

26. Protecting information systems MUST start with:
A. Buying tools
B. Risk identification
C. Incident response
D. Backup

27. Why credit card fraud is common in mobile computing?
A. Strong security
B. High user trust & weak awareness
C. Limited apps
D. Wired networks

28. Which security control is MOST effective for lost mobiles?
A. Firewall
B. IDS
C. Remote wipe
D. Sniffer

29. Wireless encryption protects against:
A. Physical theft
B. Eavesdropping
C. Malware
D. Phishing

30. Session 7 topics mainly test understanding of:
A. Programming
B. Human + wireless security risks
C. Hardware design
D. Database tuning

